    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Top displays the usage in percent of a single core. Which means 100% is one core fully utilized, 300% is three cores fully utilized. \r\nDepending on what kind of cores you have in your system we expect geth to use two ore three cores worth of CPU time.\r\nFor more info see https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/145247/understanding-cpu-while-running-top-command",
